{"created":"2015-04-03T19:55:13+00:00","modified":"2015-04-03T19:55:13+00:00","valid":{"from":"2015-04-03T19:55:13+00:00","to":"3015-04-03T19:55:13+00:00"},"hreflang":"en","guid":"0f76cd01-9d31-4870-b4ac-e838da0cae6e","title":"Making Music for Animals","published":"2015-02-09T19:23:00+00:00","teaser":"<p><a style=\"color: #e08b15; font-family: 'Open Sans', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12.960000038147px; line-height: 20.1599998474121px;\" href=\"http://animalmadness.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Laurel Braitman</a><span style=\"color: #22242f; font-family: 'Open Sans', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12.960000038147px; line-height: 20.1599998474121px;\"> is a historian of science and the author of </span><em style=\"color: #22242f; font-family: 'Open Sans', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12.960000038147px; line-height: 20.1599998474121px;\"><span class=\"book\"><a style=\"color: #e08b15;\" title=\"buy this book at Amazon\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1451627009/wnyc-s360-20/\" target=\"_blank\">Animal Madness: How Anxious Dogs, Compulsive Parrots, and Elephants in Recovery Help Us Understand Ourselves</a></span></em><span style=\"color: #22242f; font-family: 'Open Sans', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12.960000038147px; line-height: 20.1599998474121px;\">. She&rsquo;s particularly interested in animals held in captivity. &ldquo;If their minds aren&rsquo;t stimulated and challenged they can end up with all sorts of disturbing behaviors,&rdquo; she explains. Braitman wondered if music — so often soothing to people, but usually foisted on animals without their permission — could help counter animal anxiety and depression?</span></p>","itags":["npr_api","385083770"],"contentencoded":"<p><div class=\"fullattribution\">Copyright 2015 MPX. To see more, visit <a href=\"\"></a>.<img src=\"http://www.google-analytics.com/__utm.gif?utmac=UA-5828686-4&utmdt=Making+Music+for+Animals&utme=8(APIKey)9(MDAyOTcwNDAwMDEyODgyMDkwMTgwNzY3YQ001)\"/></div></p>","audio":[{"meta":{"duration":null},"type":"audio/m3u","href":"http://api.npr.org/m3u/1385083774-7a3145.m3u?orgId=30000&e=385083770&ft=nprml&f=385083770"}]}